    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-12-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-12-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="395" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d395">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. G. F. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr. Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 225.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Consulate
                                    General</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Shanghai</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-12-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 11, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to my despatch No. 188, I have
                            now the honor to forward to you a copy of a despatch which I have just
                            addressed to the minister, in the same matter, viz: the expulsion of
                            American merchants from the north bank of the Yangtsi at Chinkiang,
                            together with copies of a despatch from the Tantai at that port, dated
                            October 8, and my response of the 13th of the same month; which deal
                            with various points involved.</p>
                <p>I have the honor, <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c</hi>.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GEO. F. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
